OL,3,CJersey votes to legalise assisted dying
OL,5,FJersey has chosen to legalise assisted
OL,6,Fdying for some terminally ill
OL,7,Fresidents.
OL,9,FAfter years of debate, scrutiny and
OL,10,Fconsultations, States Members approved
OL,11,Fthe landmark legislation by 32 votes
OL,12,Fto 16.
OL,14,FThe law would allow a terminally ill
OL,15,Fperson who has been a Jersey resident
OL,16,Ffor at least a year and is
OL,17,Fexperiencing, or expected to
OL,18,Fexperience, "unbearable suffering" to
OL,19,Fchoose to end their life with the help
OL,20,Fof a willing medical professional.
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws         G1/11
OL,2,W+.!/*%/*%/*%/*%+,"-$ /(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,
