CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F386A1772399158
OL,3,CJersey votes to legalise assisted dying
OL,5,FThe second and third readings were
OL,6,Fpassed in the same States' sitting on
OL,7,FThursday 26 February.
OL,9,FJersey politicians discussed a number
OL,10,Fof amendments to the law.
OL,12,FThey rejected Deputy Baraba Ward's
OL,13,Fproposition to remove the 'waiver for
OL,14,Ffuture capacity' as she feels it
OL,15,Fleaves islanders vulnerable to
OL,16,Fcoercion, manipulation, and abuse.
OL,18,FIt means a medical professional can
OL,19,Fproceed with the assisted death, even
OL,20,Fif a person has lost capacity, if they
OL,21,Fhave previously agreed to it.
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws         G4/11
OL,2,W+.!/*%/*%/*%/*%+,"-$ /(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BCh Is News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,387,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38605
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F386A1772399158
OL,3,CJersey votes to legalise assisted dying
OL,5,FReacting to the defeated proposition,
OL,6,FDeputy Ward says: "It needed to be
OL,7,Faired because it was a concern for me,
OL,8,Fpeople voted accordingly, and I walked
OL,9,Faway positively.
OL,11,F"With 40 years of nursing, I do not
OL,12,Fsupport assisted dying; I support end-
OL,13,Fof-life care."
OL,15,FThe States approved an amendment which
OL,16,Fwill allow medical professionals to
OL,17,Fwithdraw their consent to participate
OL,18,Fin an assisted death, even if they
OL,19,Fhave previously agreed to do so.
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws         G5/11
OL,2,W+.!/*%/*%/*%/*%+,"-$ /(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,
