PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F386A1772399158
OL,3,CJersey votes to legalise assisted dying
OL,5,FThe legislation will allow terminally
OL,6,Fill people who are experiencing, or
OL,7,Fexpected to experience, "unbearable
OL,8,Fsuffering" to choose to end their life
OL,9,Fwith the help of a willing medical
OL,10,Fprofessional.
OL,12,FSomeone who requests an assisted death
OL,13,Fmust make a voluntary, clearly
OL,14,Fexpressed, settled and informed choice.
OL,16,FTwo doctors will also need to sign off
OL,17,Fon the decision and there is a legal
OL,18,Fapproval process, which will take at
OL,19,Fleast two weeks.
OL,21,FWho can apply?
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws         G9/11
OL,2,W+.!/*%/*%/*%/*%+,"-$ /(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,
